        <defect>
            <para>The rear hydraulic ABS brake hoses may rupture at any time without warning under normal driving
                conditions. Improper hose length may induce rupturing due to chafing, scraping, rubbing, or over
                extending.
                <emph type="bold">If a hose ruptures, the rear brakes will fail and could cause a vehicular accident
                    resulting in property damage, personal injury, or death.
                </emph>
            </para>
            <para>Repairs will be required on 3400, 3800, 4700, and 4900 models with rear leaf spring suspensions and
                build date combinations listed below. Each vehicle is assigned to a Repair Group below. Use the "Repair
                Group" number to reference the required repair procedure in the "Service Procedure" section of this
                letter.
            </para>
